column1: Question,Correct Answer,Wrong Answer 1,Wrong Answer 2,Wrong Answer 3
Which is true about abstract classes?,Can have both abstract and concrete methods,Must have only abstract methods,Cannot have constructors,Cannot have fields

Which is valid sealed class syntax?,"sealed class Shape permits Circle, Square {}","sealed class Shape allows Circle, Square {}","sealed class Shape extends Circle, Square {}","sealed class Shape implements Circle, Square {}"
Which statement about instanceof is correct?,Returns true if object is instance of specified type,Returns the type of object,Casts the object,Throws exception if false
Which modifier is required for a method to be overridden?,No special modifier required,final,static,private
Which is true about sealed classes?,"Permitted subclasses must be final, sealed, or non-sealed",All subclasses are implicitly final,Cannot have any subclasses,Must be abstract
Which Object method returns string representation?,toString(),getString(),print(),display()

Which is true about reference type vs object type?
Animal a = new Dog();,"Reference type is Animal, object type is Dog",Both are Animal,Both are Dog,"Reference type is Dog, object type is Animal"

Which is valid for sealed class subclass?
sealed class Shape permits Circle {},final class Circle extends Shape {},class Circle extends Shape {},abstract class Circle extends Shape {},interface Circle extends Shape {}
Which statement about hashCode() is correct?,"If equals() is overridden, hashCode() should be too",hashCode() cannot be overridden,equals() and hashCode() are unrelated,hashCode() is final in Object
Which is true about abstract methods?,Must be overridden in concrete subclass,Can have method body,Can be private,Can be final
Which is true about non-sealed classes?,Allows unlimited subclassing,Cannot be extended,Must be final,Is same as sealed
Which modifier prevents method overriding?,final,static,private,abstract
Which is true about polymorphism?,Method called determined at runtime,Method called determined at compile time,Only works with interfaces,Requires casting
Which is required for sealed class?,permits clause or subclasses in same file,extends clause,implements clause,abstract modifier
Which is true about abstract class constructors?,Can have constructors,Cannot have constructors,Constructors must be abstract,Constructors must be private
